div.div: Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu Part 2

Rudeus, Eris, and Rujierd head for Asura Kingdom in search of answers. Meanwhile, Roxy sets out across the Demon Continent to find Rudeus.
(Source: Funimation, edited)
Senpai ga Uzai Kouhai no Hanashi

Being seen as a full-fledged business woman isn’t easy for Futaba Igarashi when her senpai, Harumi, treats her like a kid. Days for her are never typical, at work or outside of it, with all the antics going on in her life. As mishaps ensue, she’ll find herself growing closer with her loudmouth senpai. Maybe Futaba feels more than she lets on, but one thing’s for sure: she’s still annoyed!
(Source: Funimation)
Monster ga Afureru Sekai ni Natta kedo, Tayoreru Neko ga Iru kara Daijoubu desu.

On her way home from shopping for dinner, Kujo Ayame, a new member of society who lives with her tortoiseshell cat, Haru, gets caught up in the drastic changes in the world. The changed cityscape, monsters attacking people, and people awakening to their skills....
In the turmoil, Ayame and Haru accidentally succeed in defeating a giant monster, and at that moment, a voice echoes in their heads. ["Kujo Ayame's LV has increased from 1 to 10"]
["Confirming the first named monster defeat in Chaos Frontier Acquired the bonus skill "Search"]
With that as a trigger, Ayame made full use of her search skill to survive in a overflowing with monsters.
Moreover, Ayame is not the only one who has awakened to this skill; her cat Haru has also acquired the useful cheat-level skill "Conversion"!
(Source: GA Novels, translated)

Deep within the deserts lie the mysterious Dungeons, vast stores of riches there for the taking by anyone lucky enough to find them and brave enough to venture into the depths from where few have ever returned. Plucky young adventurer Aladdin means to find the Dungeons and their riches, but Aladdin may be just as mysterious as the treasures he seeks. Together with the djinn Ugo and his friend Alibaba, Aladdin sets out to find his fortune in the depths of the endless dunes… (Source: Shogakukan Asia)
